It was a Sh3.6 trillion affair to a nation crippled by the coronavirus pandemic and the second budget since the first case of the virus was reported in the country in March 2020.    Here is how key ministries faired in the allocations.  Health: Sh121.1 billion to the Health sector to support of its various programmes.  Security: Sh294.5 billion was allocated to the Defence, National Police and National Intelligence Service. Transport: Sh182.5 billion  Education: Sh2.2 billion  Agriculture: Sh60b  By Stephanie Wangari | 2 hours ago By George Maringa | 3 hours ago By Wainaina Wambu | 10 hours ago By Patrick Alushula | 13 hours ago